Overview

  • Cleanup DNA using AMPure

Detailed procedure

  1. All C3D samples were qubit’d using the HS DNA detection kit.
ID ng/μL total_ng
C3D_1 31.8 954
C3D_2 36.2 1086
C3D_3 22.8 684
C3D_4 49.6 1490.7
C3D_5 53.2 1596
C3D_6 72.4 2172
C3D_7 45.6 1368
C3D_8 67.2 2016

  1. DNA chosen was C3D6, as it looked like it contained a reasonable amount of high molecular weight DNA and had a high concentration as per Qubit.

  2. AMPure clean-up using protocol PN 100-801-600 “Purify DNA”, using 0.6X beads at recommendation of Vickie. Samples were brought up to 50uL at beginning of prep, and 30uL beads were added.

  3. Qubit HS took place after clean-up, with DNA in a 40uL elution - named C3D6c.

|ID|ng/μL|total_ng|%_loss| |:—–:|:—–:|:—–:|:—–:| |C3D_6C|36.4|1456|32.97%|

  1. 0.8% gel, 60V for 2 hours ran to assess if low molecular weight DNA had been cleared.
